On the 16th anniversary of the Oklahoma City Bombing, President Obama expressed condolences to the families and friends who lost loved ones in the attack. He also highlighted the resilience and toughness of the American people and emphasized the nation's commitment to fighting terrorism and violent extremism. The President recognized the courage of first responders and the solidarity of the nation in supporting the affected community. He concluded by expressing that thoughts and prayers are still with those who lost their lives in the bombing.